        2/15/2014
    

I am rating Norv extremely poor because he is extremely non-responsive. By the way, I have never filed a claim so am an ideal customer. A copy of my policy is required to go to an Additional Interested Party. My policy says that a certificate of insurance has been sent to said party, but none seem to be received. I recently received an email from Norv requesting that I rate him "10" on an upcoming survey, and to contact them if I am not completely satisfied so they can address any concerns. I immediately replied to the email that the interested party says they have not received a certificate of insurance and to send me a copy if you did send it. No response. A few days later I received an email from Norv soliciting term life insurance. I immediately replied that he hadn't replied to my email. No response. Then I called Norv. Not in. Two weeks after my initial email, I received a call from his son saying Norv was out of town and has asked him to assist me. Based upon the above events, I have little faith that I would receive decent service in the event of a claim.




